<TITLE> Stocks stay buoyant on banks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)Markets closed up for the straight second day driven by a surge in bank prices. Banks, accounting more than 50 percent of the market capitalisation, rose more than nine percent on average with some gaining over ten percent. Social Investment Bank soared 19.96 percent while IFIC Bank , City Bank and AB Bank climbed 14.17 percent, 13.73 percent and 13.65 percent respectively. Turnover on the country's bourses also increased substantially with the Dhaka Stock Exchange crossing the Tk 5 billion mark and the port city bourse surpassing Tk 750 million. Meanwhile, insurers and non-bank financial institutions rallied Monday. Mutual funds, power, energy and pharmaceuticals continued to slide with textile shares joining the club. Brokerage house officials said textile shares lost due to the news that the government did not giving any extra benefit for the export-oriented sector in its stimulus package. The package announced Sunday to tackle the fallout of the global recession increased cash incentives for exports in jute, leather and frozen foods. Dhaka Stock Exchange Dhaka stocks saw shares worth Tk 5.42 billion changing hands, rising from Sunday's Tk 4.77 billion while turnover on the port city's bourse reached to Tk 775.933 millionsurging from 617.682 million the previous day. DSE's benchmark general index surged 65.54 points or 2.53 percent to 2653.09. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2196.93, rising 54.42 points or 2.54 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 gained 34.53 points or 1.69 percent to finish on 2066.61. Losers beat gainers 122 to 117 while seven issues held steady. Beximco emerged as the turnover leader with shares worth Tk 368.616 million changing hands. It fell 2.50 percent to Tk 244.70. AB Bank followed with a turnover of Tk 285.692 million, to surge 13.65 percent on Tk 793. Summit Power ended on Tk 1179, edging down 0.21 percent. It saw shares worth Tk 249.389 million traded. Newer entrant, Summit Alliance Port Ltd had shares worth Tk 180.261 million. It gained 9.39 percent to finish at Tk 1804.25. Titas Gas lost 1.35 percent to Tk 510.75 after Sunday's gains. Its turnover amounted to Tk 172.078 million. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardSoutheast Bank, Uttara Bank and National Bank Ltdfinished higher. Profit- taking caused ACI and Beximco Pharmaceuticals to lose. Chittagong Stock Exchange The CSCX or selective categories index rose 192.11 points or 3.57 percent to close at 5570.49. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8531.59, gaining 277.73 points or 3.36 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip shot up 305.23 points or 4.67 percent to finish at 6841.22. Of the traded issues, 75 advanced, 71 declined with three scrips unchanged. AIMS First Mutual Fund was the turnover leader with transactions of Tk 655,000 followed by Bextex Ltd, Shinepukur Ceramics, Grameen Mutual Fund One: Scheme 2, and First Security Bank.
